text.section:
This section does not apply to:
Trading stamps, as defined by § 13-101 of the Business Regulation Article;
State lottery tickets issued under the authority of Title 9, Subtitle 1 of the State Government Article;
Retail promotions, not involving the offer of gifts and prizes, which offer savings on consumer goods or services including "one-cent sales", "two-for-the-price-of-one-sales", or manufacturer's "cents-off" coupons;
Games of skill competition not involving sales promotion efforts; or
A savings promotion raffle conducted by a credit union under § 6-716 of the Financial Institutions Article or by a depository institution under § 1-211 of the Financial Institutions Article.

When a person offers prizes in a sales promotion effort relating to the sale, lease, or rental of real property not prohibited by this section, that person shall disclose to each offeree, in writing, clearly and conspicuously:
That the purpose of the sales promotion effort is to solicit the purchase, lease, or rental of real property;
The exact number of each prize offered in each category to be made available during the sales promotion;
The manufacturer's suggested retail price or comparable retail price of each prize offered;
If calculable in advance, the odds against winning each prize; or
If not calculable in advance, a statement to that effect, or that the odds of winning will be determined by the number of entries;
Whether all prizes offered will be awarded and when a determination of winners will be made; and
If prizes with retail prices or monetary values in excess of $100 are offered, where and when a list of winners of those prizes can be obtained.

If a person offers a contest, sweepstakes, or other sales promotion effort not prohibited by this section, involving the award of prizes by chance, that person shall disclose to each offeree in writing:
The exact number of each prize offered in each category to be made available during the contest, sweepstakes, or sales promotion;
The manufacturer's suggested retail price, or comparable retail price, of each prize offered;
If calculable in advance, the odds against winning each prize and if not calculable in advance, a statement that the odds of winning will be determined by the number of entries;
Whether all prizes offered will be awarded and when a determination of winners will be made;
What, if any, conditions must be met in order to receive a prize;
If prizes with retail prices or monetary values in excess of $100 are offered, where and when a list of winners of those prizes can be obtained; and
That in order to receive the prize offered in the sales promotion you may not be required to:
Purchase goods or services;
Pay any money; or
Where applicable, submit to a sales promotion effort.
